==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Woolder
<hw>Woold"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A stick used to tighten the rope in
woolding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Rope Making)</fld> <def>One of the handles of the
top, formed by a wooden pin passing through it. See 1st <er>Top</er>,
2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woolding</ent>⟦br⟧
